3. KDE Apps on GNOME (Dolphin & Konsole)
To make these look right on Kali GNOME, you need the KDE integration tools:

Bash
sudo apt install dolphin konsole qt5-style-kvantum qt6-style-kvantum -y
Dolphin Theme: Open Dolphin, go to Settings > Configure Dolphin. To make it match Catppuccin, you'll need to install the Kvantum Manager and select a Catppuccin theme there.

Konsole Theme: ```bash
mkdir -p ~/.local/share/konsole
cd ~/.local/share/konsole
wget https://www.google.com/search?q=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/catppuccin/konsole/main/themes/Mocha.colorscheme

Open Konsole -> `Settings > Edit Current Profile > Appearance` and select **Mocha**.
